emuInput.TitMainTitle: Five women, Grace Redd wearing dark dress with spaghetti straps, cross necklace, and corsage, and five men, seated at table with cake and candles, in interior with dark trimmed doors
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 1, 1941, pg. 9 reads: "Cutting Birthday Cake - Charming Miss Grace Redd of Lowell street observed her birthday Saturday with much gayety and a party to which Eddie Breckman was host. Miss Redd wore gardenias and was felicitated and showered with gifts by many friends - Harris photo."
